---
import ToolLayout from '@/layouts/ToolLayout.astro'
import { UnitConverter } from '@/components/tools/UnitConverter'
import { getToolById } from '@/data/tools'

const tool = getToolById('unit-converter')!
---

<ToolLayout tool={tool}>
  <UnitConverter client:load />

  <section slot="content" class="mt-8 prose prose-slate max-w-none">
    <h2>How to Use the Unit Converter</h2>
    <p>
      Select a category from the buttons at the top — Length, Weight, Temperature, Volume, Area, Speed, Time, or Digital Storage. The unit dropdowns will automatically populate with the available units in that category. Choose your source unit in the <strong>From</strong> dropdown, enter the value you want to convert, and select the destination unit in the <strong>To</strong> dropdown. The result appears immediately.
    </p>
    <p>
      Click the swap button (⇄) between the two panels to reverse the conversion — swapping the From and To units so you can quickly convert back. This is especially useful when you know the result but need to find the original value, such as converting kilometers back to miles after already converting miles to kilometers.
    </p>
    <p>
      The result is displayed with up to 7 significant figures, giving you a precise answer without unnecessary decimal noise. A summary line below the converter confirms the full conversion formula so you can double-check the result.
    </p>

    <h2>Unit Conversion Reference</h2>
    <p>
      The converter covers eight major categories of physical measurement:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Length:</strong> kilometers, meters, centimeters, millimeters, miles, yards, feet, and inches. Essential for travel, engineering, and everyday measurements.</li>
      <li><strong>Weight &amp; Mass:</strong> kilograms, pounds, grams, ounces, stones, and metric tons. Used in cooking, shipping, fitness, and science.</li>
      <li><strong>Temperature:</strong> Celsius, Fahrenheit, and Kelvin. Temperature uses formulas rather than simple multiplication — the converter handles all three correctly.</li>
      <li><strong>Volume:</strong> liters, gallons, milliliters, fluid ounces, cups, and tablespoons. Useful for cooking, chemistry, and fuel calculations.</li>
      <li><strong>Area:</strong> square meters, square feet, hectares, acres, square kilometers, and square miles. Important for real estate, agriculture, and mapping.</li>
      <li><strong>Speed:</strong> km/h, mph, m/s, and knots. Used in driving, aviation, sailing, and physics.</li>
      <li><strong>Time:</strong> hours, minutes, days, weeks, and years. Useful for project planning and scheduling calculations.</li>
      <li><strong>Digital Storage:</strong> kilobytes, megabytes, gigabytes, terabytes, and megabits. Essential for understanding file sizes, storage capacity, and network speeds.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      For more detailed converter pages with additional units and conversion tables, explore the individual converter pages linked in the related tools section.
    </p>

    <h2>Privacy</h2>
    <p>
      All conversions are performed locally in your browser using JavaScript math. No data is sent to any server.
    </p>
  </section>
</ToolLayout>
